data.name: Cottage Cheese Stuffed Peppers
data.quickTastyDescription: Delicious bell peppers filled with creamy cottage cheese and herbs, baked to perfection!
detailedCookingInstructions: Cut the tops off the bell peppers and remove the seeds and membranes.
In a large bowl, combine cottage cheese, shredded cheese, spinach, garlic powder, salt, and pepper. Mix well.
Stuff each bell pepper with the cottage cheese mixture until filled.
Place the stuffed peppers in a baking dish and drizzle with olive oil.
Cover the dish with aluminum foil and bake for 25 minutes.
Remove the foil and bake for an additional 5-10 minutes, until the peppers are tender and the cheese is bubbly.
data.detailedName: Baked Cottage Cheese Stuffed Bell Peppers
